Hardware Importance¶

  • Multi-faceted term of many underlying components

  • Includes CPU cores, processing speed, bit-architecture, RAM, hard disk, etc.

  • Needs vary with project (i.e., bootstrapping, replication, computing, compilation)

Benchmarking Importance¶

  • Helps target and focus resources on specific aspect

  • Guages performance across several parameters

  • Ensures stability for end use needs

alpha = 'ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789'
data_tools = ['sas', 'stata', 'spss', 'python', 'r', 'julia']
ROW_SIZE = 1E4

np.random.seed(2019)
random_df = pd.DataFrame({'group': np.random.choice(data_tools, size=int(ROW_SIZE)),
                          'float': np.random.randint(1, 15, int(ROW_SIZE)),
                          'y_num': np.random.uniform(0, 100, int(ROW_SIZE)),
                          'x_num1': np.random.uniform(0, 100, int(ROW_SIZE)),
                          'x_num2': np.random.uniform(size=int(ROW_SIZE)) * 10,
                          'x_num3': np.random.normal(10, 1, int(ROW_SIZE)),
                          'x_num4': np.random.normal(50, 1, int(ROW_SIZE)),
                          'x_num5': np.random.normal(100, 1, int(ROW_SIZE)),
                          'char': [''.join(np.random.choice(list(alpha), 3)) for _ in range(int(ROW_SIZE))],
                          'bool': np.random.choice([True, False], int(ROW_SIZE)),
                          'date': np.random.choice(pd.date_range('2000-01-01', 
                                              dt.datetime.today().strftime('%Y-%m-%d')), int(ROW_SIZE)),
                           })    

random_df.sample(10)

In [16]:
def powerset(iterable):
    "powerset([1,2,3]) --> () (1,) (2,) (3,) (1,2) (1,3) (2,3) (1,2,3)"
    s = list(iterable)
    return chain.from_iterable(combinations(s, r) for r in range(len(s)+1))

expvar_list = filter(len, powerset(['x_num'+str(i) for i in range(1,6)]))
formulas_list = ['y_num ~ {} + group'.format(" + ".join(f)) for f in list(expvar_list)]

formulas_list

coeff_dfs = [pd.DataFrame({'coeff': m.params, 
                               't_stats': m.tvalues,
                               'std_err': m.bse,
                               'p_values': m.pvalues,
                               'low_ci': m.conf_int()[0],
                               'high_ci': m.conf_int()[1]}) for m in models]
    
anova_dfs = [pd.DataFrame({'obs': m.nobs,
                           'df_resid': m.df_resid,
                           'r_sq': m.rsquared,
                           'r_sq_adj': m.rsquared_adj,
                           'f_value': m.fvalue,
                           'f_pvalue': m.f_pvalue,
                           'ssr': m.ssr,
                           'ess': m.ess,
                           'mse_model': m.mse_model,
                           'mse_resid': m.mse_resid,
                           'mse_total': m.mse_total}, index=[0]) for m in models]

plot_results = []

for m in models:
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15,5))

    sns.barplot(x=m.params[1:].index, y=m.params[1:])

    plt.title('Barplot of Coefficients', weight='bold', size=18)
    plt.xlabel('Explanatory Variables', weight='bold', size=16)
    plt.ylabel('Estimate', weight='bold', size=16)
    plt.xticks(ha='center')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plot_results.append(fig)
        
    plt.clf()
    plt.close('all')

free_data = pd.DataFrame({'mem_total': np.nan, 'mem_used': np.nan, 'mem_free': np.nan,
                          'swap_total': np.nan, 'swap_used': np.nan, 'swap_free': np.nan,
                          'cpu_cores': np.nan, 'cpu_speed': np.nan
                         }, index=[0])
    
free_raw = tuple(map(int, os.popen('free').readlines()[1].split()[1:])) 
swap_raw = tuple(map(int, os.popen('free').readlines()[2].split()[1:])) 

free_data['mem_total'] = free_raw[0] / 1E3 
free_data['mem_used'] = free_raw[1] / 1E3
free_data['mem_free'] = free_raw[2] / 1E3
free_data['swap_total'] = swap_raw[0] / 1E3
free_data['swap_used'] = swap_raw[1] / 1E3
free_data['swap_free'] = swap_raw[2] / 1E3

Memory Used¶

In [76]:
import psutil

## rss: aka “Resident Set Size”, this is the non-swapped physical memory a process has used. 
## vms: aka “Virtual Memory Size”, this is the total amount of virtual memory used by the process.
    
process = psutil.Process(os.getpid()).memory_info()  

sys_data = sys_data.join(pd.DataFrame({'physical_memory_used': process.rss / 1E6, 
                                       'virtual_memory_used': process.vms / 1E6
                                      }, index=[0])
                        )

sys_data

Timings¶

In [ ]:
from timeit import Timer

f = Timer("machine_run()", "from __main__ import machine_run")
res = f.repeat(repeat=5, number=1)

sys_data = sys_data.join(pd.DataFrame({'min': np.min(res),
                                       'mean': np.mean(res),
                                       'median': np.median(res),
                                       'max': np.max(res),
                                       'neval': 5}, index=[0])
                        )

Plotting by Metrics¶

In [10]:
fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(18,6))
ax2 = ax1.twinx()

(results_df.set_index('time_stamp')
           .plot(kind='line', style='.-', y='mean', ax=ax1, color=sns.color_palette('deep')[0])
)
(results_df.set_index('time_stamp')
           .plot(kind='line', style='.-', y='physical_memory_used', ax=ax2, color=sns.color_palette('deep')[1])
)
(results_df.set_index('time_stamp')
           .plot(kind='line', style='.-', y='virtual_memory_used', ax=ax2, color=sns.color_palette('deep')[2])
)

ax1.set_xlabel('Script Date/Time')
ax1.legend(loc='upper left')
ax1.set_ylabel('Script Runtime (sec)', weight='bold', size=18)

ax2.set_ylabel('Memory (MB)', weight='bold', size=18)
ax2.legend(loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(0, 0.93))
plt.title('Memory Usage and Timings Over Script Iterations', weight='bold', size=24)

plt.show()
plt.clf()
plt.close()
In [12]:
for row_idx, grp_df in results_df.groupby('row_size'):
    fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(18,6))
    ax2 = ax1.twinx()

    (grp_df.set_index('time_stamp')
               .plot(kind='line', style='.-', y='mean', ax=ax1, color=sns.color_palette('deep')[0])
    )
    (grp_df.set_index('time_stamp')
               .plot(kind='line', style='.-', y='physical_memory_used', ax=ax2, color=sns.color_palette('deep')[1])
    )
    (grp_df.set_index('time_stamp')
               .plot(kind='line', style='.-', y='virtual_memory_used', ax=ax2, color=sns.color_palette('deep')[2])
    )

    ax1.set_xlabel('Script Date/Time')
    ax1.legend(loc='upper left')
    ax1.set_ylabel('Script Runtime (sec)', weight='bold', size=18)

    ax2.set_ylabel('Memory (MB)', weight='bold', size=18)
    ax2.legend(loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(0, 0.93))
    plt.title('Memory Usage and Timings Over Script Runs,\nRow Size: {:,}'.format(row_idx), weight='bold', size=24)

    plt.show()
    plt.clf()
    plt.close()
